    <abstract>
      <t>The delivery of value-added services relies on the invocation of advanced Service Functions in a sequential order. This mechanism is called Service Function Chaining (SFC). The set of involved Service Functions and their order depends on the service context and other deployment-specific considerations. This document presents a set of general use cases of Service Function Chaining (SFC).</t>
